    {
      "note_no": "20",
      "note": "In its primary sense, the term sawm denotes \"abstinence\" or \"self-denial\"; in the present context it is synonymous with samt (\"abstinence from speech\"); in fact - as pointed out by Zamakhshari - the latter term is said to have figured in the Qur'an - copy belonging to 'Abd Allah ibn Mas'ad (possibly as a marginal, explanatory notation)."
    }
